00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:30,710
No, no. We're fine. We're fine.

763
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:34,870
Well, I just knocked over this Go board.
Sorry about that.

764
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:36,710
- Everyone's all right?
- Yeah, fine.

765
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:39,070
No, no. Go to bed, Joni.

766
00:39:39,160 --> 00:39:40,790
Okay.

767
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:43,150
Maybe we can talk tomorrow
about the family...

768
00:39:43,240 --> 00:39:44,640
Tomorrow's fine.

769
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:47,590
- Good night. Love you. Night.
- Love you. Bye.

770
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:51,960
Come on.

771
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:54,670
Pay attention, now.

772
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:58,790
Your mom is still undocumented.

773
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:00,430
And if this is your fault,

774
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:03,080
she'll be found out and at best deported,

775
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:05,150
and your family will be broken.

776
00:40:05,240 --> 00:40:08,230
We're not gonna let that happen,
are we, huh?

777
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:10,470
But you have to do exactly
what I tell you.

778
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:12,950
Will you do this, Marta?

779
00:40:14,680 --> 00:40:15,790
This last thing...

780
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:18,830
for me, for your family?

781
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,150
What do you want me to do?

782
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:28,790
<i>Go downstairs as noisily as you can</i>

783
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:30,360
<i>and then say goodbye loudly.</i>

784
00:40:30,440 --> 00:40:31,550
Walt, I'm leaving.

785
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:34,310
<i>- Call attention to the time...</i>
- God, it's midnight already.

786
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,510
<i>...if you can.</i>

787
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:38,510
<i>Drive out the gate.</i>

788
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:40,470
<i>Then to avoid the security cameras,</i>

789
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:43,550
<i>pull off the road
before the carved elephant.</i>

790
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:48,310
- Wait. Was it before or after?
<i>- After the carved elephant.</i>

791
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:50,430
No, he said before. Was it?

792
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:53,240
<i>- Beafterfore the carved elephant.</i>
- Oh, shit.

793
00:40:56,840 --> 00:41:00,510
<i>Park, and come back
on foot up to the house.</i>

794
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:04,310
<i>Take the side yard pass
through the little gate.</i>

795
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:07,070
<i>The dogs will know you.
They shouldn't bark.</i>

796
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:12,510
<i>You've got to get up to the third floor
without being seen.</i>

797
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:14,830
<i>And the only way
is to climb the side trellis</i>

798
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:17,310
<i>and come in through the trick hall window.</i>

799
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:19,110
You gotta be kidding me.

800
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:20,870
<i>I am not. Do it.</i>

801
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:32,830
<i>And for God's sake, don't make any noise!</i>

802
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:45,870
<i>Once you're inside,
and this is the tricky part...</i>

803
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:47,280
<i>This is the tricky part?</i>

804
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:50,790
<i>Get my robe and cap from my bedroom</i>

805
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:52,310
<i>and put them on.</i>

806
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,430
<i>Harlan...</i>

807
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:55,350
This is crazy.
I don't think I can do that.

808
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:58,310
No, we need to make this so airtight
that the average cop

809
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:00,790
will entirely dismiss you as a suspect.

810
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:03,110
It sounds crazy, but it'll work.

811
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:10,560
<i>Walt is smoking outside, and he'll see you</i>

812
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,120
<i>through the glazed window.</i>

813
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:15,270
Dad? Go back to bed.

814
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:18,200
<i>You were seen leaving.</i>

815
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:20,740
<i>The security cameras show you driving off.</i>

816
00:42:20,840 --> 00:42:22,430
<i>And 20 minutes later,</i>

817
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:25,470
<i>I'm seen alive and well by my son.</i>

818
00:42:25,560 --> 00:42:29,030
<i>You see,
you've gone from suspect number one</i>

819
00:42:29,120 --> 00:42:30,910
<i>to an impossibility.</i>

820
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:32,510
<i>Leave the way you came</i>

821
00:42:32,840 --> 00:42:35,750
<i>and don't be seen.</i>

822
00:42:46,120 --> 00:42:47,630
Ransom?

823
00:42:49,080 --> 00:42:51,150
Are you back again already?

824
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:55,950
<i>Drive home.</i>

825
00:42:56,440 --> 00:43:00,320
<i>And sometime in the next few days,
the police will question you.</i>

826
00:43:00,760 --> 00:43:03,030
No. No, no, no.

827
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:04,670
No, I can't lie!

828
00:43:05,360 --> 00:43:07,230
You know I can't lie! I'll puke!

829
00:43:07,320 --> 00:43:10,070
Well, then don't lie.
Tell fragments of the truth.

830
00:43:10,160 --> 00:43:11,560
In this exact order.

831
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:20,310
I took him upstairs.

832
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:23,710
We played our nightly game of Go.

833
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:27,990
At some point, he knocked the board over

834
00:43:28,080 --> 00:43:30,990
and Joni came up to check on us.

835
00:43:34,720 --> 00:43:36,310
I gave him pain medication.

836
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:39,910
He pulled his shoulder last week.

837
00:43:41,480 --> 00:43:43,830
And I left him in his study.

838
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:45,820
At midnight

839
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:47,070
I said goodbye to Walt...

840
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:50,470
went home.

841
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:52,200
What kind of medication did you give him?

842
00:43:55,800 --> 00:44:00,470
Since his injury, I've been giving him
100 milligram IV push of Toradol.

843
00:44:00,920 --> 00:44:02,590
It's a non-narcotic analgesic.

844
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:04,990
And to help him sleep,

845
00:44:05,120 --> 00:44:07,230
three milligrams of morphine.

846
00:44:07,320 --> 00:44:09,030
And the family was aware of this?

847
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:10,760
Yes, of course.

848
00:44:10,840 --> 00:44:14,590
Did you notice anything strange
or off about his demeanor?

849
00:44:18,520 --> 00:44:19,590
No.

850
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:25,430
Well, that sounds about right.

851
00:44:26,920 --> 00:44:28,270
Thank you, Miss Cabrera.

852
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:50,630
Hey, sis, people are gonna get here
for the memorial pretty soon.

853
00:44:50,720 --> 00:44:51,720
Are you...

854
00:44:54,680 --> 00:44:56,000
Are you all right?

855
00:44:56,560 --> 00:44:58,830
I was just thinking about Dad's games.

856
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:02,480
This all feels like one.

857
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:06,080
Like something he'd write, not do.

858
00:45:07,160 --> 00:45:09,910
I keep waiting for the big reveal.

859
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:13,280
Where it'll make sense.

860
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:15,550
Wouldn't that be nice?

861
00:45:16,760 --> 00:45:17,830
Oh, Walt.

862
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:22,830
<i>I don't think he killed himself.</i>

863
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,590
I don't. I really don't.

864
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:27,190
There's this Hallmark movie

865
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:29,550
called <i>Deadly by Surprise</i>
with Danica McKellar.

866
00:45:29,640 --> 00:45:33,600
And in it, she plays this wife
who's getting poisoned by her husband,

867
00:45:33,680 --> 00:45:36,270
but he's doing it little by little,
so she doesn't know it

868
00:45:36,360 --> 00:45:38,750
and she goes crazy, and she kills herself.

869
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:42,310
And my cousin, who's a receptionist
at the medical examiner's office,

870
00:45:42,400 --> 00:45:44,350
she says that stuff totally happens.

871
00:45:44,440 --> 00:45:47,630
It's not even 3% as crazy as
the stuff she's seen come through there.

872
00:45:47,720 --> 00:45:48,750
So, I'm just like...

873
00:45:50,280 --> 00:45:51,950
Oh, God, yeah!

874
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:54,150
I mean, don't like him
because you love him.

875
00:45:54,240 --> 00:45:56,990
No, I don't like him. He's an asshole.

876
00:45:57,080 --> 00:45:59,270
But maybe an asshole is what we needed.

877
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:00,950
Oh, my God, yeah,

878
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:02,630
an asshole is what Germany needed

879
00:46:02,720 --> 00:46:04,550
- in 1930-whatever.
- Here we go.

880
00:46:04,640 --> 00:46:06,680
Come on, Joni, those two things
don't even conflate.

881
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:09,150
- There is the problem right there.
- Jesus.

882
00:46:09,800 --> 00:46:12,260
I'm gonna disappear
until the politics talk is done.

883
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:13,760
You want some champers?

884
00:46:14,440 --> 00:46:16,230
I can't. I'm technically working.

885
00:46:16,320 --> 00:46:19,430
Why don't you take off your red cap,
Richard, and look around you?

886
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:21,350
The streets are literally
flooded with Nazis.

887
00:46:21,440 --> 00:46:22,840
No, no, no. No, no, no.

888
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:25,950
We are losing our way of life
and our culture.

889
00:46:26,040 --> 00:46:27,550
- That's right.
- There are millions

890
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:29,240
- of Mexicans coming.
- Oh, God, really?

891
00:46:29,320 --> 00:46:31,690
Don't make this a race thing.
You always make this a race thing.

892
00:46:31,720 --> 00:46:34,110
I would say the same thing
if they were European immigrants.

893
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:36,310
Oh, yeah? So, if the Swiss were, like,

894
00:46:36,400 --> 00:46:38,400
- clogging in the streets...
- No, we allow them in

895
00:46:38,480 --> 00:46:40,710
and they think they own what's ours.

896
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:43,910
They're putting children in cages!
I mean, these are camps!

897
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,510
Come on, Joni,
nobody's saying that isn't bad,

898
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:48,790
but the parents have some blame here.

899
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:51,310
Oh, for what? For wanting
a better life for their kids?

900
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:54,190
- Isn't that what America is...
- For breaking the law!

901
00:46:54,280 --> 00:46:56,740
- My God.
- You're gonna hate hearing this,

902
00:46:56,840 --> 00:46:59,710
- but it's true, America is for Americans.
- Don't point at me.

903
00:46:59,800 --> 00:47:02,470
- Where's Marta? Is she still here? Marta!
- Oh, God, don't.

904
00:47:02,560 --> 00:47:03,880
- Come on over.
- No, Richard.

905
00:47:03,960 --> 00:47:06,390
- Come on over, Marta. Please.
- You're shitting me.

906
00:47:06,480 --> 00:47:07,800
Marta,

907
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:11,760
your family is from Uruguay,
but you did it right.

908
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:14,230
I mean, what I'm saying is
they did it legally.

909
00:47:14,320 --> 00:47:16,190
She did it the right way.

910
00:47:16,280 --> 00:47:20,190
You work hard, and you'll earn your share
from the ground up.

911
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:24,350
Just like Dad and like all the rest of us.
And I'll bet you agree with me, right?

912
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:26,870
Oh, just leave the poor girl alone,
Richard.

913
00:47:26,960 --> 00:47:29,470
It's okay! I just wanna hear
what she has to say!

914
00:47:29,560 --> 00:47:30,840
It's okay, Marta, you can speak.

915
00:47:30,880 --> 00:47:32,770
Sweetheart, don't feel
pressure to answer. This is just...

916
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:33,720
Look.

917
00:47:33,720 --> 00:47:36,510
- Please don't.
- If you wanna become an American,

918
00:47:36,600 --> 00:47:39,060
there are legal ways to do it.

919
00:47:39,160 --> 00:47:43,040
But if you break the law,
it doesn't matter how good your heart is,

920
00:47:43,120 --> 00:47:45,790
you gotta face the consequences!

921
00:47:45,880 --> 00:47:47,360
Are you goddamn insane?

922
00:47:47,440 --> 00:47:49,630
- It's done.
- Hey! I'm warning you.

923
00:47:55,600 --> 00:47:58,910
That's when I ask her, "Tonya,
what is wrong with people?" Literally.

924
00:47:59,600 --> 00:48:01,950
Oh, my God! Marta, what?

925
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:03,310
Marta?

926
00:48:03,440 --> 00:48:04,510
What's the matter?

927
00:48:04,600 --> 00:48:06,750
Whoa, whoa. Hey. Breathe.

928
00:48:06,840 --> 00:48:08,790
- Oh, my gosh.
- Marta, are you okay?

929
00:48:09,840 --> 00:48:12,030
Hey, Fran, do you still have your stash?

930
00:48:17,560 --> 00:48:19,040
Take 'em whenever you need 'em.

931
00:48:19,120 --> 00:48:21,550
They're just drying out
since you gave me that Juul.

932
00:48:21,640 --> 00:48:23,040
Thanks, Fran.

933
00:48:23,120 --> 00:48:24,910
- Hey. Hey.
- I'm sorry.

934
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:26,000
- No, just...
- I'm sorry.

935
00:48:26,080 --> 00:48:27,300
I'm very, very sorry.

936
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:29,550
- Stop saying you're sorry. Jesus!
- I hate this.

937
00:48:29,640 --> 00:48:32,280
Oh, God, my heart won't stop. I can't...

938
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:35,630
It's just everything... No, thank you.

939
00:48:38,600 --> 00:48:40,510
That's where Fran keeps her stash?

940
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:43,750
Who's gonna open a clock?

941
00:48:45,320 --> 00:48:46,830
Do you want dinner, Nana?

942
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:49,070
Dinner? To eat?

943
00:48:49,560 --> 00:48:51,470
- To eat?
- Walt.

944
00:48:51,560 --> 00:48:53,040
- Nana?
- Walt, Walt, she's fine.

945
00:48:53,120 --> 00:48:55,310
She ate the entire salmon spread already.

946
00:48:57,120 --> 00:48:59,710
Walt? Did you tell Marta yet,
what we all talked about?

947
00:48:59,800 --> 00:49:01,590
No, not yet. Is now a good time?

948
00:49:01,680 --> 00:49:03,630
Yes. Yes, a very good time, right now.

949
00:49:03,720 --> 00:49:05,120
Oh, okay.

950
00:49:05,560 --> 00:49:07,190
All right. Calm down.

951
00:49:09,520 --> 00:49:10,630
Marta,

952
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:13,700
we've been talking it over and...

953
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:17,830
- Have you been smoking grass?
- No.

954
00:49:18,920 --> 00:49:19,920
Come on.

955
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:21,630
Marta, we've been talking it over,

956
00:49:21,720 --> 00:49:23,750
and the whole family,

957
00:49:24,240 --> 00:49:26,030
we'd like to take care of you.

958
00:49:26,920 --> 00:49:28,830
Wha... What does that mean?

959
00:49:30,120 --> 00:49:32,070
We all think that you deserve something.

960
00:49:32,160 --> 00:49:34,230
Financially we'd like to help you out.

961
00:49:34,680 --> 00:49:36,990
You were never anything but good to Dad

962
00:49:37,760 --> 00:49:39,470
and because of that we...

963
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:41,870
You can count on us.

964
00:49:42,840 --> 00:49:43,870
Yeah.

965
00:49:46,320 --> 00:49:48,630
I thought you should've been
at the funeral.

966
00:49:48,720 --> 00:49:50,630
By the way, I was outvoted.

967
00:50:01,680 --> 00:50:02,870
Detective.

968
00:50:04,080 --> 00:50:05,080
You're still here?

969
00:50:11,760 --> 00:50:13,030
Did you know Harlan?

970
00:50:13,560 --> 00:50:16,870
He knew my father,
who was a police detective years ago.

971
00:50:19,480 --> 00:50:20,990
My father respected Harlan.

972
00:50:21,720 --> 00:50:23,550
That says quite a lot.

973
00:50:23,640 --> 00:50:24,990
Is that why you're here?

974
00:50:26,480 --> 00:50:28,150
Here now, here?

975
00:50:28,240 --> 00:50:29,640
No.

976
00:50:30,360 --> 00:50:32,390
I stayed hoping to speak to you
a little more.

977
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:40,950
Something is afoot with this whole affair.

978
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:43,470
I know it.

979
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:45,950
I believe you know it, too.

980
00:50:47,800 --> 00:50:49,020
So you're gonna keep digging?

981
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:53,230
Harlan's detectives, they dig.

982
00:50:53,840 --> 00:50:55,630
They rifle and root.

983
00:50:56,080 --> 00:50:57,350
Truffle pigs.

984
00:50:59,120 --> 00:51:03,000
I anticipate the terminus
of <i>Gravity's Rainbow.</i>

985
00:51:03,880 --> 00:51:05,070
<i>Gravity's Rainbow?</i>

986
00:51:05,640 --> 00:51:06,910
It's a novel.

987
00:51:07,040 --> 00:51:08,310
Yeah, I know.

988
00:51:08,800 --> 00:51:10,910
- I haven't read it though.
- Neither have I.

989
00:51:11,280 --> 00:51:13,630
Nobody has. But I like the title.

990
00:51:14,680 --> 00:51:19,270
It describes the path of a projectile
determined by natural law.

991
00:51:19,360 --> 00:51:21,710
<i>Et voilÃ ,</i> my method.

992
00:51:21,800 --> 00:51:25,910
I observe the facts
without biases of the head or heart.

993
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:30,070
I determine the arc's path,
stroll leisurely to its terminus,

994
00:51:30,680 --> 00:51:33,240
and the truth falls at my feet.

995
00:51:35,800 --> 00:51:39,070
The medical examiner was ready
to rule this a suicide,

996
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:42,190
but Elliott agreed to keep it pending
for 48 hours.

997
00:51:42,800 --> 00:51:45,190
Tomorrow morning,
I search the grounds and the house,

998
00:51:45,280 --> 00:51:46,790
begin my investigation.

999
00:51:47,920 --> 00:51:49,990
I want you to be by my side for it.

1000
00:51:50,440 --> 00:51:51,550
- What?
- My confidante.

1001
00:51:51,640 --> 00:51:54,430
- My eyes and ears.
- Hey. Wait, wait, Detective. Why me?

1002
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:57,190
I trust your kind heart.

1003
00:51:59,160 --> 00:52:01,920
Also, you're the only one who had nothing
to gain from Harlan's death.

1004
00:52:03,560 --> 00:52:04,880
So how about it, Watson?

1005
00:52:05,880 --> 00:52:07,150
Hey, Detective?

1006
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:09,470
If you want my insight into the family...

1007
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:12,240
None of them are murderers.

1008
00:52:12,920 --> 00:52:14,110
