01:34:03,160 --> 01:34:05,270
- Mr. Drysdale, come on.
- Let's go.

1764
01:34:06,160 --> 01:34:08,880
- Pat him down, check him out.
- What's going on?

1765
01:34:09,560 --> 01:34:12,430
- "Ransom came back," she said.
- Hands on the vehicle.

1766
01:34:12,520 --> 01:34:14,830
I don't know what he came back to do,
but we'll find out.

1767
01:34:14,960 --> 01:34:16,150
You got anything sharp?

1768
01:34:17,440 --> 01:34:20,190
- Watch your head. Thank you.
- Hey, you don't need to thank him.

1769
01:34:20,280 --> 01:34:23,510
Did he ask you to drive
when he saw me coming?

1770
01:34:25,080 --> 01:34:26,150
Yes.

1771
01:34:33,760 --> 01:34:35,190
Blanc, coming with us?

1772
01:34:35,280 --> 01:34:36,710
I'll drive with Marta.

1773
01:34:37,640 --> 01:34:39,150
Let's go to the police station.

1774
01:34:39,240 --> 01:34:42,670
I want a full rundown
on everything he said to you.

1775
01:34:42,760 --> 01:34:44,350
I'll catch you up on where we're at.

1776
01:34:51,480 --> 01:34:54,150
Strange case from the start.

1777
01:34:55,400 --> 01:34:58,390
A case with a hole in the middle.

1778
01:35:00,280 --> 01:35:01,280
A doughnut.

1779
01:35:02,680 --> 01:35:05,110
I'm just talking through my process here.

1780
01:35:05,200 --> 01:35:06,990
Let me know if this is boring.

1781
01:35:07,720 --> 01:35:09,350
I feel the noose tightening.

1782
01:35:09,880 --> 01:35:12,310
The family is truly desperate.

1783
01:35:13,040 --> 01:35:14,670
Desperate motives.

1784
01:35:15,360 --> 01:35:17,470
The mystery of who hired me.

1785
01:35:17,560 --> 01:35:19,190
The impossibility of the crime.

1786
01:35:20,400 --> 01:35:21,590
And yet...

1787
01:35:22,760 --> 01:35:24,510
A doughnut.

1788
01:35:24,600 --> 01:35:27,110
One central piece.

1789
01:35:27,240 --> 01:35:30,310
And if it reveals itself,
the fog would lift,

1790
01:35:30,400 --> 01:35:34,510
the arc would resolve,
the Slinky become unkinked.

1791
01:35:34,600 --> 01:35:36,550
Do you mind if I stop for a second?

1792
01:35:36,640 --> 01:35:38,150
I need to pick something up.

1793
01:35:38,240 --> 01:35:39,670
It'll be very quick.

1794
01:35:40,920 --> 01:35:42,070
Sure.

1795
01:35:55,640 --> 01:35:56,960
It'll be just a few minutes.

1796
01:35:57,040 --> 01:35:58,230
Watch the...

1797
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:00,000
door.

1798
01:36:22,480 --> 01:36:23,480
Hello?

1799
01:36:47,400 --> 01:36:49,350
Listen, I don't know what you want.

1800
01:36:52,080 --> 01:36:53,990
Whatever it is, we can work it out.

1801
01:36:54,120 --> 01:36:56,680
But we have to figure it out
right here, right now.

1802
01:36:56,760 --> 01:36:58,430
And I'm leaving with that report.

1803
01:37:03,160 --> 01:37:04,270
Hello?

1804
01:37:29,560 --> 01:37:30,750
Fran?

1805
01:37:40,560 --> 01:37:42,310
No, no, no, no! Fran?

1806
01:37:43,960 --> 01:37:45,180
Oh, my God, Fran.

1807
01:37:45,280 --> 01:37:46,310
Can you hear me?

1808
01:37:47,080 --> 01:37:49,230
Fran, give me a sign if you can hear me.

1809
01:37:49,320 --> 01:37:51,470
- You...
- Yes, it's me. It's Marta.

1810
01:37:51,560 --> 01:37:53,430
You called me here, you sent me an e-mail.

1811
01:37:53,520 --> 01:37:55,630
That's why I'm here.
Did you take something?

1812
01:37:55,720 --> 01:37:58,070
I'm gonna call an ambulance now.
You're gonna be okay.

1813
01:37:58,160 --> 01:37:59,870
You're gonna be fine, okay? Stay with me.

1814
01:37:59,960 --> 01:38:01,180
- Copy...
- What?

1815
01:38:01,280 --> 01:38:02,310
Copy...

1816
01:38:03,160 --> 01:38:04,270
Stashed...

1817
01:38:04,360 --> 01:38:05,710
What? What are you saying?

1818
01:38:07,080 --> 01:38:08,630
You did this.

1819
01:38:09,360 --> 01:38:11,390
Won't get away with this.

1820
01:38:11,480 --> 01:38:12,670
Jesus, stop it!

1821
01:38:35,000 --> 01:38:36,830
<i>911, what's your emergency?</i>

1822
01:38:38,240 --> 01:38:42,990
<i>The thought of you stays bright</i>

1823
01:38:44,520 --> 01:38:49,190
<i>Sometimes I stand
In the middle of the floor</i>

1824
01:38:50,800 --> 01:38:54,580
<i>Not going left</i>

1825
01:38:55,880 --> 01:38:56,910
<i>Not going...</i>

1826
01:38:57,000 --> 01:38:58,220
Oh, Lord.

1827
01:39:00,440 --> 01:39:02,950
All right, my friend.
Thank you for the update.

1828
01:39:04,160 --> 01:39:05,190
There's no need for that.

1829
01:39:05,280 --> 01:39:08,630
I'll bring her in once we get word
that the housekeeper is stable.

1830
01:39:08,720 --> 01:39:10,040
It's still touch and go.

1831
01:39:10,600 --> 01:39:11,600
All right.

1832
01:39:13,120 --> 01:39:14,190
Listen, this is over.

1833
01:39:14,280 --> 01:39:15,790
People are getting hurt.

1834
01:39:18,440 --> 01:39:19,760
So I'm gonna tell you the truth.

1835
01:39:19,840 --> 01:39:23,390
Young Ransom just told
Lieutenant Elliott everything.

1836
01:39:24,040 --> 01:39:25,040
Good.

1837
01:39:25,120 --> 01:39:27,110
Wait, I hope he didn't cover for me.

1838
01:39:27,200 --> 01:39:28,680
Did he tell you the real truth

1839
01:39:28,760 --> 01:39:30,750
- about me switching the...
- Yeah.

1840
01:39:30,840 --> 01:39:32,110
- And the disguise bit?
- Yes.

1841
01:39:32,200 --> 01:39:34,190
And the whole blackmail and...

1842
01:39:35,200 --> 01:39:37,430
But why did Fran take my morphine?

1843
01:39:37,520 --> 01:39:39,830
I mean, obviously she had swiped
the bag from the house,

1844
01:39:39,920 --> 01:39:41,870
but she didn't seem like a user to me,

1845
01:39:41,960 --> 01:39:43,950
unless that's why she needed
the blackmail money.

1846
01:39:44,080 --> 01:39:46,350
I don't know. It doesn't matter anyway.

1847
01:39:46,440 --> 01:39:49,120
I have to tell the Thrombeys myself.
I feel like I owe that to them.

1848
01:39:49,200 --> 01:39:50,550
I don't think that's a good idea.

1849
01:39:50,640 --> 01:39:52,990
No, I have to do it. I need to do it.

1850
01:39:55,000 --> 01:39:56,400
I gave the doctors my number,

1851
01:39:56,480 --> 01:39:58,280
so they'll call if anything
changes with Fran.

1852
01:39:58,360 --> 01:39:59,360
All right.

1853
01:39:59,440 --> 01:40:02,670
I'll round up the Thrombeys at the house,
along with a police escort.

1854
01:40:03,240 --> 01:40:04,720
For the arrest after.

1855
01:40:05,840 --> 01:40:07,840
You can tell me your whole story
on the drive over.

1856
01:40:09,200 --> 01:40:11,070
I don't want any more surprises.

1857
01:40:26,880 --> 01:40:30,470
Fran said it was stashed,
the copy, and then she said,

1858
01:40:31,080 --> 01:40:33,270
"You did this.
You won't get away with it."

1859
01:40:33,360 --> 01:40:36,030
And I called the ambulance.

1860
01:40:36,680 --> 01:40:37,790
That's it.

1861
01:40:39,080 --> 01:40:40,110
All right.

1862
01:40:42,280 --> 01:40:43,390
You ready?

1863
01:40:50,640 --> 01:40:51,830
Okay.

1864
01:40:52,400 --> 01:40:54,030
Well, has she come to her senses?

1865
01:40:54,120 --> 01:40:56,770
Well, she's standing right there, Richard.
She can speak for herself.

1866
01:40:56,800 --> 01:40:58,960
- Is the rest of the family here?
- In the living room.

1867
01:40:59,000 --> 01:41:02,390
I think that it would be better if we were
to gather again and get this over with.

1868
01:41:08,040 --> 01:41:09,440
- Hey.
- Hey.

1869
01:41:11,720 --> 01:41:13,590
I'm so sorry I told them about your mom.

1870
01:41:13,680 --> 01:41:15,350
Meg, it's okay.

1871
01:41:16,240 --> 01:41:18,840
I'm sorry. No... I was scared.
I just... I didn't wanna tell them.

1872
01:41:18,920 --> 01:41:20,430
I get it.

1873
01:41:20,520 --> 01:41:21,790
Trust me.

1874
01:41:22,520 --> 01:41:24,550
I understand. It's all right.

1875
01:41:25,720 --> 01:41:26,720
I'm sorry.

1876
01:41:30,000 --> 01:41:32,720
God, I am so raiding
Fran's stash after this.

1877
01:41:32,800 --> 01:41:35,260
I still think this is a bad idea,

1878
01:41:35,960 --> 01:41:38,070
but the family is assembled.

1879
01:41:41,480 --> 01:41:43,230
I know where the tox report is.

1880
01:41:50,880 --> 01:41:52,470
She basically told me where it was.

1881
01:41:55,120 --> 01:41:56,950
Anyways, this will tie everything up.

1882
01:41:59,280 --> 01:42:00,910
And I just handed it to you.

1883
01:42:02,400 --> 01:42:04,790
God, you're not much
of a detective, are you?

1884
01:42:05,440 --> 01:42:06,990
Well, to be fair...

1885
01:42:08,880 --> 01:42:11,230
you make a pretty lousy murderer.

1886
01:42:13,280 --> 01:42:14,950
Perhaps we deserve each other.

1887
01:42:27,240 --> 01:42:28,790
You've always been good to me.

1888
01:42:30,800 --> 01:42:32,910
And what I'm about to say
isn't gonna be easy

1889
01:42:33,040 --> 01:42:34,520
and you're gonna be upset.

1890
01:42:35,480 --> 01:42:38,270
But I thought after what you've
gone through the last few days,

1891
01:42:39,560 --> 01:42:41,870
that you deserved to hear it from me.

1892
01:42:44,960 --> 01:42:46,180
- I...
- Excuse me!

1893
01:42:50,680 --> 01:42:52,950
You have not been good to her.

1894
01:42:53,760 --> 01:42:55,830
You have all treated her like shit,

1895
01:42:55,920 --> 01:42:59,430
to steal back a fortune that you lost
and she deserves.

1896
01:43:00,160 --> 01:43:03,070
You're a pack of vultures at the feast!

1897
01:43:03,160 --> 01:43:04,950
Knives out, beaks bloody!

1898
01:43:05,040 --> 01:43:06,440
Well...

1899
01:43:07,080 --> 01:43:09,670
You're not getting bailed out,
not this time.

1900
01:43:10,720 --> 01:43:14,790
Miss Cabrera has decided, definitively,
not to renounce the inheritance.

1901
01:43:15,320 --> 01:43:17,030
- What?
- What?

1902
01:43:17,120 --> 01:43:20,150
Furthermore, it will be
my professional recommendation

1903
01:43:20,240 --> 01:43:22,350
to the local authorities
that the manner of death

1904
01:43:22,440 --> 01:43:26,550
in the case of Harlan Thrombey
is ruled as suicide!

1905
01:43:26,640 --> 01:43:28,120
- And the case is closed.
- Blanc?

1906
01:43:28,200 --> 01:43:30,990
- What?
- Thank you all for coming. Goodbye.

1907
01:43:31,080 --> 01:43:32,480
What's going on? Just tell me...

1908
01:43:34,560 --> 01:43:37,200
That's certainly not what I was expecting.

1909
01:43:37,280 --> 01:43:39,550
- No.
- Is anybody else confused?

1910
01:43:39,640 --> 01:43:41,670
Not what I was expecting to hear at all.

1911
01:43:44,360 --> 01:43:46,050
Are you gonna tell me
what the hell is going on?

1912
01:43:46,080 --> 01:43:48,910
- Yes. Yes.
- I just wanna come clean, okay?

1913
01:43:49,000 --> 01:43:50,320
- It's over.
- Almost.

1914
01:43:50,400 --> 01:43:51,670
Blanc, what are we doing?

1915
01:43:51,760 --> 01:43:54,150
- What's going on?
- I'm sorry. Officer Wagner.

1916
01:43:54,240 --> 01:43:57,310
Keep the family out of this room,
and get 'em out of the house if you can.

1917
01:43:57,400 --> 01:43:59,470
But stand by with your additional officer.

1918
01:43:59,560 --> 01:44:00,590
Get the family out?

1919
01:44:00,680 --> 01:44:02,390
Yes, but not all of them. Would you...

1920
01:44:02,480 --> 01:44:03,480
Thank you.

1921
01:44:03,520 --> 01:44:04,710
- Blanc.
- Yes, sir.

1922
01:44:04,840 --> 01:44:06,270
Come on, what's all this drama?

1923
01:44:06,360 --> 01:44:08,030
- Indulge me.
- Blanc,

1924
01:44:08,120 --> 01:44:11,630
I told Ransom, Ransom told you,
and I'm telling you now,

1925
01:44:11,720 --> 01:44:14,550
it is an immovable fact
that I killed Harlan.

1926
01:44:14,640 --> 01:44:17,150
Yes, you did. Yes, he did. Yes, you are.

1927
01:44:17,240 --> 01:44:20,430
But... But, I spoke in the car
about the hole

1928
01:44:20,520 --> 01:44:22,070
at the center of this doughnut.

1929
01:44:22,680 --> 01:44:25,240
And what you and Harlan did
that fateful night

1930
01:44:25,360 --> 01:44:28,510
seems at first glance
to fill that hole perfectly.

1931
01:44:28,600 --> 01:44:31,350
A doughnut hole in a doughnut's hole.

1932
01:44:31,840 --> 01:44:34,190
But we must look a little closer.

1933
01:44:34,600 --> 01:44:37,190
And when we do, we see the doughnut hole

1934
01:44:37,640 --> 01:44:39,430
has a hole in its center.

1935
01:44:39,880 --> 01:44:42,030
It is not a doughnut hole,

1936
01:44:42,120 --> 01:44:44,990
but a smaller doughnut with its own hole

1937
01:44:45,080 --> 01:44:47,870
and our doughnut is not whole at all!

1938
01:44:47,960 --> 01:44:50,130
Blanc, look, I understand
that this is amusing for you...

1939
01:44:50,160 --> 01:44:52,390
Why was I hired?

1940
01:44:53,240 --> 01:44:54,830
Why would someone hire me?

1941
01:44:54,920 --> 01:44:57,670
Someone fishing for a crime
to reverse the will. Come on.

1942
01:44:57,760 --> 01:45:00,070
But I was hired
before the sealed will was read.

1943
01:45:00,160 --> 01:45:04,510
So, yes, the person must have known
the contents of the will.

1944
01:45:04,600 --> 01:45:06,000
But one step further.

1945
01:45:06,080 --> 01:45:08,990
That same person must have known
a crime was committed,

1946
01:45:09,080 --> 01:45:10,560
and further...

1947
01:45:11,000 --> 01:45:15,270
If the intent was to reverse
Marta's inheritance,

1948
01:45:16,000 --> 01:45:18,750
they must have known
that Marta was responsible.

1949
01:45:19,160 --> 01:45:21,510
An intriguing combination of factors.

1950
01:45:21,600 --> 01:45:24,870
Someone who knew what Marta did
wanted to expose it

1951
01:45:24,960 --> 01:45:26,910
but could not reveal how they knew.

1952
01:45:27,000 --> 01:45:28,270
Fran!

1953
01:45:28,360 --> 01:45:31,110
She was blackmailing me.
She knew what I did.

1954
01:45:31,200 --> 01:45:34,870
Yeah, but Fran wanted money,
ergo she did not want the crime exposed.

1955
01:45:35,000 --> 01:45:37,890
What if someone in the family had observed
Marta doing something suspicious?

1956
01:45:37,920 --> 01:45:40,990
But they would have had
no reason not to speak up.

1957
01:45:42,760 --> 01:45:46,350
The answer is not so simple.

1958
01:45:46,920 --> 01:45:51,230
Now with the entire solution
in my field of view,

1959
01:45:51,320 --> 01:45:54,310
the arc of this case
is a tragedy of errors.

1960
01:45:56,680 --> 01:45:58,990
Marta, it will not be easy
for you to hear.

1961
01:45:59,760 --> 01:46:02,190
But there is at least

1962
01:46:02,680 --> 01:46:05,240
one truly guilty party behind it all,

1963
01:46:05,320 --> 01:46:08,430
guilty in the true sense
of acting with malice

1964
01:46:09,160 --> 01:46:12,110
and committing a heinous crime
with selfish intent.

1965
01:46:14,880 --> 01:46:16,100
Trooper Wagner.

1966
01:46:16,200 --> 01:46:17,710
Trooper Wagner?

1967
01:46:18,880 --> 01:46:19,880
No.

1968
01:46:22,240 --> 01:46:24,350
Marta, I'm so sorry.
I told them everything.

1969
01:46:24,480 --> 01:46:25,910
I figured it was up. I'm sorry.

1970
01:46:26,000 --> 01:46:28,390
Hey. It's all right, Ransom,
I'm glad you did.

1971
01:46:28,480 --> 01:46:30,550
Not exactly everything though.

1972
01:46:30,960 --> 01:46:32,910
Is this about what Greatnana told you?

1973
01:46:33,360 --> 01:46:36,150
She saw me that night.
She mistook me for Ransom.

1974
01:46:36,240 --> 01:46:37,240
We'll get to that.

1975
01:46:37,320 --> 01:46:38,720
In the meanwhile,

1976
01:46:39,440 --> 01:46:41,590
Mr. Hugh Ransom Drysdale,

1977
01:46:42,200 --> 01:46:45,910
you might tell us all why you hired me.

1978
01:46:49,320 --> 01:46:50,590
Why I hired you?

1979
01:46:51,400 --> 01:46:54,830
You're right. Let's back it up
to the night of the party.

1980
01:46:55,200 --> 01:46:57,150
<i>Your argument with Harlan.</i>

1981
01:46:57,800 --> 01:46:59,200
What were the overheard words

1982
01:46:59,280 --> 01:47:01,790
by the Nazi child
masturbating in the bathroom?

1983
01:47:02,400 --> 01:47:05,870
<i>"My will," and "I'm warning you."</i>

1984
01:47:05,960 --> 01:47:08,470
You and Harlan were drama mamas.

1985
01:47:08,560 --> 01:47:11,430
You shared a love of twisting the knife
into one another.

1986
01:47:11,520 --> 01:47:14,550
You see, I don't believe
he would have slipped it in halfway.

1987
01:47:14,640 --> 01:47:15,640
No, no, no.

1988
01:47:16,520 --> 01:47:17,590
I submit

1989
01:47:18,280 --> 01:47:20,740
Harlan told you everything.

1990
01:47:20,840 --> 01:47:22,110
You can't be serious!

1991
01:47:22,200 --> 01:47:28,110
Not a red dime or word of my work
to a single one of them, you included.

1992
01:47:28,560 --> 01:47:29,590
Marta,

1993
01:47:30,000 --> 01:47:33,510
remind me what Ransom said
his conversation with Harlan ended with?

1994
01:47:34,640 --> 01:47:36,990
Harlan told him that
I could beat him at Go.

1995
01:47:37,080 --> 01:47:40,150
And I asked myself, "Marta?

1996
01:47:40,240 --> 01:47:44,750
Why would the topic of the will
have steered around to Marta?"

1997
01:47:46,120 --> 01:47:49,110
There is one obvious explanation.

1998
01:47:49,200 --> 01:47:52,070
You can't be that crazy. You're not
just gonna throw away your fortune.

1999
01:47:52,160 --> 01:47:54,110
No. I'm giving it to Marta.

2000
01:47:54,200 --> 01:47:55,600
All of it.

2001
01:47:56,800 --> 01:47:57,910
Your Brazilian nurse?

2002
01:47:58,000 --> 01:47:59,430
Are you goddamn insane?

2003
01:47:59,520 --> 01:48:02,510
I'm sane for the first time in my life,
and I've done it.

2004
01:48:02,600 --> 01:48:04,230
If you think I'm gonna let this happen,

2005
01:48:04,320 --> 01:48:06,610
- if you think I'll stand here...
- I've made the change to my will.

2006
01:48:06,640 --> 01:48:08,630
- It's done.
- I'm warning you!

2007
01:48:10,000 --> 01:48:11,670
